{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01V8PKidQnoeNHcjMQL17q4C","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The webhook is configured with `failurePolicy: Fail` which means if the webhook denies the request, it's blocked. The webhook runs in the ingress-nginx-controller pods.\n\nLet me think about this differently. The `allow-snippet-annotations: \"true\"` in the ConfigMap should be read by the controller/webhook. But maybe there's an issue with how the controller reads this at startup vs at webhook call time.\n\nActually, I just realized something important. The ingress-nginx controller in v1.14.1 might have completely removed the `allow-snippet-annotations` ConfigMap behavior and replaced it with the CLI flag. \n\nI could try removing the ValidatingWebhookConfiguration entirely so the ingress annotations aren't validated at admission time, then apply the annotation and let the controller process it directly. The tradeoff is that invalid configurations won't be caught early, but that's acceptable for now. Though I'm second-guessing this approach since the controller error I saw earlier happened before I even applied any annotation, so removing the webhook might not solve the underlying issue.\n\nLet me trace through the logs more carefully to understand why the controller flagged rate-api as invalid in the first place.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":949,"cache_read_input_tokens":62587,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":949},"output_tokens":37,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"17a1dcd0-36fc-4f74-b9af-7bcabd04af45","uuid":"14d8408c-d659-427c-8eac-da33cbe4a3e3","request_id":"req_011Cc14X7iiQoYjB9UEzHivT"}
